    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="514"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d514">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/864.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Smith</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In view of the long interval which has elapsed without reply to its
                    representations of March 2, the Department finds itself compelled, in view of
                    interests of certain American citizens which are suffering from this delay,
                    again to call the attention of the Government of Haiti to its previous
                    representations. You will present the substance of this instruction to the
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs in the form of a memorandum and you will urge an
                    immediate reply be made.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
